composable NAME) pair mounted on either engine, compare mount DENSITY (mounts on a route /
STATE dumps recorded on that route by that engine) as an EXACT fractions.Fraction between
engines, restricted to MUTUAL ROUTES ONLY (refinement (2): kt's and py's walks have
different step budgets/state sets -- 21 kt states / 17 py states in this hostrun, and py's
BFS-replay walk redumps routes many more times than kt's single-visit walk -- so raw GLOBAL
mount totals are NOT COMPARABLE and are reported as context only, never a verdict input;
see diff_file_kind_pairs_counts()'s docstring / module comment "DENSITY VERDICTS" for the
exact rule). A pair with no mutual-route overlap where both sides have a computable
density is NOT COMPARABLE, reported separately, never folded into AGREE or DIFFER. No
